{"id":"233555817_Inverse_system_of_a_symbolic_power_III_Thin_algebras_and_fat_points","abstract":"We state a conjectural upper bound for the Hilbert function of the ideal &jnodot;_P^{(a)} of functions vanishing to order at leat `a' at a set P of s generic points of P^n, and verify the bound in some cases. We show that if 3n, s<2^n, and a is sufficiently large, then &jnodot;_P^{(a)} is never in µ-generic position (Theorem 1). R. Fröberg has given conjectural lower bounds on the Hilbert function of ideals generated by generic homogeneous polynomials, and thus also for ideals of powers of linear forms; our method is to translate these bounds to the vanishing problem, using Macaulay's inverse systems. We give an application to bounding the dimensions of spline functions for certain polyhedra in ^n, using a result of L. Rose relating these dimensions to the number of syzygies of power algebras.","authors":["IARROBINO A"],"meta":["September 1997Compositio Mathematica 108(3):319-355","DOI:10.1023/A:1000155612073"],"references":["248676097_The_geometry_of_rational_surfaces_and_Hilbert_functions_of_points_in_the_plane","223640742_Thin_algebras_of_embedding_dimension_three","290827547_Generation_de_certain_fibres_sur_les_spaces_projectifs_et_application","287179739_The_linear_syzygies_of_generic_forms","284878617_Une_conjecture_pour_la_cohomologie_des_diviseurs_sur_les_surfaces_rationnelles_generiques","268681253_On_the_14th_problem_of_Hilbert","268670912_Points_in_good_position_in_P_2","265681800_Geometrie_des_points_epais","265681799_Polynomial_interpolation_in_several_variables","265426436_An_inequality_for_Hilbert_series_of_graded_algebras","265333624_Singularites_imposables_en_position_generale_a_une_hypersurface_projective_Singularities_imposable_in_general_position_on_a_projective_surface","264960174_The_blowing_up_Horace_method_Application_to_interpolation_in_degree_four_La_methode_d'Horace_eclatee_Application_a_l'interpolation_en_degre_quatre","247897911_The_ideal_of